quran[178]{c,v,t}:
  29,46,"Do not argue with the People of the Book unless gracefully, except with those of them who act wrongfully. And say, ‚ÄúWe believe in what has been revealed to us and what was revealed to you. Our God and your God is ňĻonlyňļ One. And to Him we ňĻfullyňļ submit.‚ÄĚ"
  29,47,"Similarly ňĻto earlier messengersňļ, We have revealed to you a Book ňĻO Prophetňļ. ňĻThe faithful ofňļ those to whom We gave the Scriptures believe in it, as do some of these ňĻpagan Arabsňļ. And none denies Our revelations except the ňĻstubbornňļ disbelievers"
  29,48,"You ňĻO Prophetňļ could not read any writing ňĻevenňļ before this ňĻrevelationňļ, nor could you write at all. Otherwise, the people of falsehood would have been suspicious"
  29,49,But this ňĻQuranňļ is ňĻa set ofňļ clear revelations ňĻpreservedňļ in the hearts of those gifted with knowledge. And none denies Our revelations except the ňĻstubbornňļ wrongdoers
  29,50,"They say, ‚ÄúIf only ňĻsomeňļ signs had been sent down to him from his Lord!‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSigns are only with Allah. And I am only sent with a clear warning.‚ÄĚ"
  29,51,"Is it not enough for them that We have sent down to you the Book, ňĻwhich isňļ recited to them. Surely in this ňĻQuranňļ is a mercy and reminder for people who believe"
  29,52,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSufficient is Allah as a Witness between me and you. He ňĻfullyňļ knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And those who believe in falsehood and disbelieve in Allah, it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ losers.‚ÄĚ"
  29,53,"They challenge you ňĻO Prophetňļ to hasten the punishment. Had it not been for a time already set, the punishment would have certainly come to them ňĻat onceňļ. But it will definitely take them by surprise when they least expect it"
  29,54,They urge you to hasten the punishment. And Hell will certainly encompass the disbelievers
  29,55,"on the Day the punishment will overwhelm them from above them and from below their feet. And it will be said, ‚ÄúReap what you sowed.‚ÄĚ"
  29,56,"O My believing servants! My earth is truly spacious, so worship Me ňĻaloneňļ"
  29,57,"Every soul will taste death, then to Us you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  29,58,"ňĻAs forňļ those who believe and do good, We will certainly house them in ňĻelevatedňļ mansions in Paradise, under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work ňĻrighteousness!ňļ‚ÄĒ"
  29,59,"those who patiently endure, and put their trust in their Lord"
  29,60,"How many are the creatures that cannot secure their provisions! ňĻIt isňļ Allah ňĻWhoňļ provides for them and you ňĻas wellňļ. He is indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  29,61,"If you ask them ňĻO Prophetňļ who created the heavens and the earth and subjected the sun and the moon ňĻfor your benefitňļ, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúAllah!‚ÄĚ How can they then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  29,62,Allah gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. Surely Allah has ňĻfullňļ knowledge of everything
  29,63,"And if you ask them who sends down rain from the sky, giving life to the earth after its death, they will surely say, ‚ÄúAllah!‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúPraise be to Allah!‚ÄĚ In fact, most of them do not understand"
  29,64,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement. But the Hereafter is indeed the real life, if only they knew"
  29,65,"If they happen to be aboard a ship ňĻcaught in a stormňļ, they cry out to Allah ňĻaloneňļ in sincere devotion. But as soon as He delivers them ňĻsafelyňļ to shore, they associate ňĻothers with Him once againňļ"
  29,66,"So let them be ungrateful for all We have given them, and ňĻlet themňļ enjoy themselves ňĻfor nowňļ! For they will soon know"
  29,67,"Have they not seen how We have made ňĻMeccaňļ a safe haven, whereas people ňĻallňļ around them are snatched away?¬†How can they then believe in falsehood¬†and deny Allah‚Äôs favours"
  29,68,And who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah or reject the truth after it has reached them? Is Hell not a ňĻfittingňļ home for the disbelievers
  29,69,"As for those who struggle in Our cause, We will surely guide them along Our Way. And Allah is certainly with the good-doers"
  30,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  30,2,The Romans have been defeated
  30,3,"in a nearby land.¬†Yet following their defeat, they will triumph"
  30,4,within three to nine years.¬†The ňĻwholeňļ matter rests with Allah before and after ňĻvictoryňļ. And on that day the believers will rejoice
  30,5,"at the victory willed by Allah. He gives victory to whoever He wills. For He is the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  30,6,ňĻThis isňļ the promise of Allah. ňĻAndňļ Allah never fails in His promise. But most people do not know
  30,7,"They ňĻonlyňļ know the worldly affairs of this life, but are ňĻtotallyňļ oblivious to the Hereafter"
  30,8,Have they not reflected upon their own being? Allah only created the heavens and the earth and everything in between for a purpose and an appointed term. Yet most people are truly in denial of the meeting with their Lord
  30,9,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them? They were far superior in might; they cultivated the land and developed it more than these ňĻMeccansňļ ever have. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs. Allah would have never wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  30,10,Then most evil was the end of the evildoers for denying and mocking the signs of Allah
  30,11,"It is Allah Who originates the creation, and will resurrect it. And then to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  30,12,"On the Day the Hour will arrive, the wicked will be dumbstruck"
  30,13,"There will be no intercessors for them from among their associate-gods, and they will ňĻtotallyňļ deny their associate-gods"
  30,14,"And on the Day the Hour will arrive, the people will then be split ňĻinto two groupsňļ"
  30,15,"As for those who believed and did good, they will be rejoicing in a Garden"
  30,16,"And as for those who disbelieved, and denied Our signs and the meeting ňĻwith Allahňļ in the Hereafter, they will be confined in punishment"
  30,17,So glorify Allah in the evening and in the morning‚ÄĒ
  30,18,"all praise is for Him in the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒas well as in the afternoon, and at noon"
  30,19,He brings forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. And He gives life to the earth after its death. And so will you be brought forth ňĻfrom the graveňļ
  30,20,"One of His signs is that He created you from dust, then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒyou are human beings spreading over ňĻthe earthňļ"
  30,21,And one of His signs is that He created for you spouses from among yourselves so that you may find comfort in them. And He has placed between you compassion and mercy. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect
  30,22,"And one of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the diversity of your languages and colours. Surely in this are signs for those of ňĻsoundňļ knowledge"
  30,23,And one of His signs is your sleep by night and by day ňĻfor restňļ as well as your seeking His bounty ňĻin bothňļ. Surely in this are signs for people who listen
  30,24,"And one of His signs is that He shows you lightning, inspiring ňĻyou withňļ hope and fear.¬†And He sends down rain from the sky, reviving the earth after its death. Surely in this are signs for people who understand"
  30,25,"And one of His signs is that the heavens and the earth persist by His command. Then when He calls you out of the earth just once, you will instantly come forth"
  30,26,And to Him belong all those in the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒall are subject to His Will
  30,27,"And He is the One Who originates the creation then will resurrect it‚ÄĒwhich is even easier for Him.¬†To Him belong the finest attributes in the heavens and the earth. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  30,28,"He sets forth for you an example ňĻdrawnňļ from your own lives: would you allow some of those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in your possession to be your equal partners in whatever ňĻwealthňļ We have provided you, keeping them in mind as you are mindful of your peers?¬†This is how We make the signs clear for people who understand"
  30,29,"In fact, the wrongdoers merely follow their desires with no knowledge. Who then can guide those Allah has left to stray? They will have no helpers"
  30,30,"So be steadfast in faith in all uprightness ňĻO Prophetňļ‚ÄĒthe natural Way of Allah which He has instilled in ňĻallňļ people. Let there be no change in this creation of Allah. That is the Straight Way, but most people do not know"
  30,31,"ňĻO believers!ňļ Always turn to Him ňĻin repentanceňļ, be mindful of Him, and establish prayers. And do not be polytheists‚ÄĒ"
  30,32,"ňĻlikeňļ those who have divided their faith and split into sects, each rejoicing in what they have"
  30,33,"When people are touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ňĻaloneňļ. But as soon as He gives them a taste of His mercy, a group of them associates ňĻothersňļ with their Lord ňĻin worshipňļ"
  30,34,"becoming ungrateful for whatever ňĻfavoursňļ We have given them. So enjoy yourselves, for soon you will know"
  30,35,Or have We sent down to them an authority which attests to what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ
  30,36,"If We give people a taste of mercy, they become prideful ňĻbecauseňļ of it. But if they are afflicted with an evil for what their hands have done, they instantly fall into despair"
  30,37,Have they not seen that Allah gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills? Surely in this are signs for people who believe
  30,38,"So give your close relatives their due, as well as the poor and the ňĻneedyňļ traveller. That is best for those who seek the pleasure of Allah,¬†and it is they who will be successful"
  30,39,"Whatever loans you give, ňĻonlyňļ seeking interest at the expense of people‚Äôs wealth¬†will not increase with Allah. But whatever charity you give, ňĻonlyňļ seeking the pleasure of Allah‚ÄĒit is they whose reward will be multiplied"
  30,40,"It is Allah Who created you, then gives you provisions, then will cause you to die, and then will bring you back to life. Can any of your associate-gods do any of this? Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate with Him ňĻin worshipňļ"
  30,41,"Corruption has spread on land and sea as a result of what people‚Äôs hands have done, so that Allah may cause them to taste ňĻthe consequences ofňļ some of their deeds and perhaps they might return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  30,42,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúTravel throughout the land and see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before ňĻyouňļ‚ÄĒmost of them were polytheists.‚ÄĚ"
  30,43,"So be steadfast in the Upright Faith ňĻO Prophetňļ, before the coming of a Day from Allah that cannot be averted. On that Day the people will be divided"
  30,44,those who disbelieved will bear ňĻthe burden ofňļ their own disbelief; and those who did good will have prepared for themselves ňĻeternal homesňļ
  30,45,"so that He may ňĻgenerouslyňļ reward those who believe and do good, out of His grace. He truly does not like the disbelievers"
  30,46,"And one of His signs is that He sends the winds, ushering in good news ňĻof rainňļ so that He may give you a taste of His mercy, and that ships may sail by His command, and that you may seek His bounty, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  30,47,"Indeed, We sent before you ňĻO Prophetňļ messengers, each to their own people, and they came to them with clear proofs. Then We inflicted punishment upon those who persisted in wickedness. For it is Our duty to help the believers"
  30,48,"It is Allah Who sends the winds, which then stir up ňĻvapour, formingňļ clouds, which He then spreads out in the sky or piles up into masses as He wills, from which you see rain come forth. Then as soon as He causes it to fall on whoever He wills of His servants, they rejoice"
  30,49,although they had utterly lost hope just before it was sent down to them
  30,50,"See then the impact of Allah‚Äôs mercy: how He gives life to the earth after its death! Surely That ňĻsame Godňļ can raise the dead. For He is Most Capable of everything"
  30,51,"Then if We send a ňĻharshňļ wind which they see withering ňĻtheirňļ crops, they will definitely deny ňĻold favoursňļ right after"
  30,52,So you ňĻO Prophetňļ certainly cannot make the dead hear ňĻthe truthňļ. Nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away
  30,53,"Nor can you lead the blind out of their misguidance. You can make none hear ňĻthe truthňļ except those who believe in Our revelations, ňĻfullyňļ submitting ňĻto Allahňļ"
  30,54,"It is Allah Who created you in a state of weakness, then developed ňĻyourňļ weakness into strength, then developed ňĻyourňļ strength into weakness and old age.¬†He creates whatever He wills. For He is the All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  30,55,"And on the Day the Hour will arrive, the wicked will swear that they did not stay ňĻin this worldňļ more than an hour. In this way they were always deluded ňĻin the worldňļ"
  30,56,"But those gifted with knowledge and faith will say ňĻto themňļ, ‚ÄúYou did actually stay‚ÄĒas destined by Allah‚ÄĒuntil the Day of Resurrection. So here is the Day of Resurrection ňĻwhich you deniedňļ! But you did not know ňĻit was trueňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  30,57,"So on that Day the wrongdoers‚Äô excuses will not benefit them, nor will they be allowed to appease ňĻtheir Lordňļ"
  30,58,"We have certainly set forth every ňĻkind ofňļ lesson for people in this Quran. And no matter what sign you bring to them ňĻO Prophetňļ, the disbelievers will definitely say ňĻto the believersňļ, ‚ÄúYou are only a people of falsehood.‚ÄĚ"
  30,59,This is how Allah seals the hearts of those unwilling to know ňĻthe truthňļ
  30,60,"So be patient, for the promise of Allah certainly is true. And do not be disturbed by those who have no sure faith"
  31,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  31,2,"These are the verses of the Book, rich in wisdom"
  31,3,ňĻIt isňļ a guide and mercy for the good-doers‚ÄĒ
  31,4,"those who establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  31,5,"It is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ guided by their Lord, and it is they who will be successful"
  31,6,"But there are some who employ theatrics,¬†only to lead others away from Allah‚Äôs Way‚ÄĒwithout any knowledge‚ÄĒand to make a mockery of it. They will suffer¬†a humiliating punishment"
  31,7,"Whenever Our revelations are recited to them, they turn away in arrogance as if they did not hear them, as if there is deafness in their ears. So give them good news ňĻO Prophetňļ of a painful punishment"
  31,8,Surely those who believe and do good will have the Gardens of Bliss
  31,9,"staying there forever. Allah‚Äôs promise is true. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  31,10,"He created the heavens without pillars‚ÄĒas you can see‚ÄĒand placed firm mountains upon the earth so it does not shake with you, and scattered throughout it all types of creatures. And We send down rain from the sky, causing every type of fine plant to grow on earth"
  31,11,"This is Allah‚Äôs creation. Now show Me what those ňĻgodsňļ other than Him have created. In fact, the wrongdoers are clearly astray"
  31,12,"Indeed, We blessed Luqm√Ęn with wisdom, ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúBe grateful to Allah, for whoever is grateful, it is only for their own good. And whoever is ungrateful, then surely Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy.‚ÄĚ"
  31,13,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Luqm√Ęn said to his son, while advising him, ‚ÄúO my dear son! Never associate ňĻanythingňļ with Allah ňĻin worshipňļ, for associating ňĻothers with Himňļ is truly the worst of all wrongs.‚ÄĚ"
  31,14,"And We have commanded people to ňĻhonourňļ their parents. Their mothers bore them through hardship upon hardship, and their weaning takes two years. So be grateful to Me and your parents.¬†To Me is the final return"
  31,15,"But if they pressure you to associate with Me what you have no knowledge of,¬†do not obey them. Still keep their company in this world courteously, and follow the way of those who turn to Me ňĻin devotionňļ. Then to Me you will ňĻallňļ return, and then I will inform you of what you used to do"
  31,16,"ňĻLuqm√Ęn added,ňļ ‚ÄúO my dear son! ňĻEvenňļ if a deed were the weight of a mustard seed‚ÄĒbe it ňĻhiddenňļ in a rock or in the heavens or the earth‚ÄĒAllah will bring it forth. Surely Allah is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  31,17,"‚ÄúO my dear son! Establish prayer, encourage what is good and forbid what is evil, and endure patiently whatever befalls you. Surely this is a resolve to aspire to"
  31,18,"‚ÄúAnd do not turn your nose up to people, nor walk pridefully upon the earth. Surely Allah does not like whoever is arrogant, boastful"
  31,19,"Be moderate in your pace. And lower your voice, for the ugliest of all voices is certainly the braying of donkeys.‚ÄĚ"
  31,20,"Have you not seen that Allah has subjected for you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth, and has lavished His favours upon you, both seen and unseen? ňĻStillňļ there are some who dispute about Allah without knowledge, or guidance, or an enlightening scripture"
  31,21,"When it is said to them, ‚ÄúFollow what Allah has revealed,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúNo! We ňĻonlyňļ follow what we found our forefathers practicing.‚ÄĚ ňĻWould they still do soňļ even if Satan is inviting them to the torment of the Blaze"
  31,22,"Whoever fully submits themselves to Allah and is a good-doer, they have certainly grasped the firmest hand-hold. And with Allah rests the outcome of ňĻallňļ affairs"
  31,23,"But whoever disbelieves, do not let their disbelief grieve you ňĻO Prophetňļ. To Us is their return, and We will inform them of all they did. Surely Allah knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  31,24,"We allow them enjoyment for a little while, then ňĻin timeňļ We will force them into a harsh torment"
  31,25,"And if you ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will definitely say, ‚ÄúAllah!‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúPraise be to Allah!‚ÄĚ In fact, most of them do not know"
  31,26,"To Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. Allah is truly the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  31,27,"If all the trees on earth were pens and the ocean ňĻwere inkňļ, refilled by seven other oceans, the Words of Allah would not be exhausted. Surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  31,28,"The creation and resurrection of you ňĻallňļ is as simple ňĻfor Himňļ as that of a single soul. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  31,29,"Do you not see that Allah causes the night to merge into the day and the day into the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term, and that Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  31,30,"That is because Allah ňĻaloneňļ is the Truth and what they invoke besides Him is falsehood, and ňĻbecauseňļ Allah ňĻaloneňļ is the Most High, All-Great"
  31,31,"Do you not see that the ships sail ňĻsmoothlyňļ through the sea by the grace of Allah so that He may show you some of His signs? Surely in this are signs for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  31,32,"And as soon as they are overwhelmed by waves like mountains, they cry out to Allah ňĻaloneňļ in sincere devotion. But when He delivers them ňĻsafelyňļ to shore, only some become relatively grateful. And none rejects Our signs except whoever is deceitful, ungrateful"
  31,33,"O humanity! Be mindful of your Lord, and beware of a Day when no parent will be of any benefit to their child, nor will a child be of any benefit to their parent. Surely Allah‚Äôs promise is true. So do not let the life of this world deceive you, nor let the Chief Deceiver¬†deceive you about Allah"
  31,34,"Indeed, Allah ňĻaloneňļ has the knowledge of the Hour. He sends down the rain,¬†and knows what is in the wombs.¬†No soul knows what it will earn for tomorrow, and no soul knows in what land it will die. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  32,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  32,2,The revelation of this Book is‚ÄĒbeyond doubt‚ÄĒfrom the Lord of all worlds
  32,3,"Or do they say, ‚ÄúHe has fabricated it!‚ÄĚ? No! It is the truth from your Lord in order for you to warn a people to whom no warner has come before you, so they may be ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  32,4,"It is Allah Who has created the heavens and the earth and everything in between in six Days,¬†then established Himself on the Throne. You have no protector or intercessor besides Him. Will you not then be mindful"
  32,5,"He conducts every affair from the heavens to the earth, then it all ascends to Him on a Day whose length is a thousand years by your counting"
  32,6,"That is the Knower of the seen and unseen‚ÄĒthe Almighty, Most Merciful"
  32,7,Who has perfected everything He created. And He originated the creation of humankind from clay
  32,8,Then He made his descendants from an extract of a humble fluid
  32,9,"then He fashioned them and had a spirit of His Own ňĻcreationňļ breathed into them. And He gave you hearing, sight, and intellect. ňĻYetňļ you hardly give any thanks"
  32,10,"ňĻStillňļ they ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhen we are disintegrated into the earth, will we really be raised as a new creation?‚ÄĚ In fact, they are in denial of the meeting with their Lord"
  32,11,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYour soul will be taken by the Angel of Death, who is in charge of you. Then to your Lord you will ňĻallňļ be returned.‚ÄĚ"
  32,12,"If only you could see the wicked hanging their heads ňĻin shameňļ before their Lord, ňĻcrying:ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! We have now seen and heard, so send us back and we will do good. We truly have sure faith ňĻnowňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  32,13,"Had We willed, We could have easily imposed guidance on every soul. But My Word will come to pass: I will surely fill up Hell with jinn and humans all together"
  32,14,So taste ňĻthe punishmentňļ for neglecting the meeting of this Day of yours. We ňĻtooňļ will certainly neglect you. And taste the torment of eternity for what you used to do
  32,15,The only ňĻtrueňļ believers in Our revelation are those who‚ÄĒwhen it is recited to them‚ÄĒfall into prostration and glorify the praises of their Lord and are not too proud
  32,16,"They abandon their beds, invoking their Lord with hope and fear, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  32,17,No soul can imagine what delights are kept in store for them as a reward for what they used to do
  32,18,Is the one who is a believer equal ňĻbefore Allahňļ to the one who is rebellious? They are not equal
  32,19,"As for those who believe and do good, they will have the Gardens of ňĻEternalňļ Residence‚ÄĒas an accommodation for what they used to do"
  32,20,"But as for those who are rebellious, the Fire will be their home. Whenever they try to escape from it, they will be forced back into it, and will be told, ‚ÄúTaste the Fire‚Äôs torment, which you used to deny.‚ÄĚ"
  32,21,"We will certainly make them taste some of the minor torment ňĻin this lifeňļ before the major torment ňĻof the Hereafterňļ, so perhaps they will return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  32,22,And who does more wrong than the one who is reminded of Allah‚Äôs revelations then turns away from them? We will surely inflict punishment upon the wicked
  32,23,"Indeed, We gave the Scripture to Moses‚ÄĒso let there be no doubt ňĻO Prophetňļ that you ňĻtooňļ are receiving revelations‚ÄĒand We made it a guide for the Children of Israel"
  32,24,"We raised from among them leaders,¬†guiding by Our command, when they patiently endured and firmly believed in Our signs"
  32,25,"Indeed, your Lord will decide between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their differences"
  32,26,"Is it not yet clear to them how many peoples We destroyed before them, whose ruins they still pass by? Surely in this are signs. Will they not then listen"
  32,27,"Do they not see how We drive rain to parched land, producing ňĻvariousňļ crops from which they and their cattle eat? Will they not then see"
  32,28,"They ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhen is this ňĻDay of finalňļ Decision, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  32,29,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúOn the Day of Decision it will not benefit the disbelievers to believe then, nor will they be delayed ňĻfrom punishmentňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  32,30,"So turn away from them, and wait! They too are waiting"
  33,1,"O Prophet! ňĻAlwaysňļ be mindful of Allah, and do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  33,2,Follow what is revealed to you from your Lord. Surely Allah is All-Aware of what you ňĻallňļ do
  33,3,"And put your trust in Allah, for Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,4,"Allah does not place two hearts in any person‚Äôs chest. Nor does He regard your wives as ňĻunlawful for you likeňļ your real mothers, ňĻevenňļ if you say they are.¬†Nor does He regard your adopted children as your real children.¬†These are only your baseless assertions. But Allah declares the truth, and He ňĻaloneňļ guides to the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  33,5,"Let your adopted children keep their family names. That is more just in the sight of Allah. But if you do not know their fathers, then they are ňĻsimplyňļ your fellow believers and close associates. There is no blame on you for what you do by mistake, but ňĻonlyňļ for what you do intentionally. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,6,"The Prophet has a stronger affinity to the believers than they do themselves. And his wives are their mothers. As ordained by Allah, blood relatives are more entitled ňĻto inheritanceňļ than ňĻotherňļ believers and immigrants, unless you ňĻwant toňļ show kindness to your ňĻcloseňļ associates ňĻthrough bequestňļ.¬†This is decreed in the Record"
  33,7,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from the prophets, as well as from you ňĻO Prophetňļ, and from Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, son of Mary. We did take a solemn covenant from ňĻall ofňļ them"
  33,8,so that He may question these men of truth about their ňĻdelivery of theňļ truth. And He has prepared a painful punishment for the disbelievers
  33,9,"O believers! Remember Allah‚Äôs favour upon you when ňĻenemyňļ forces came to ňĻbesiegeňļ you ňĻin Medinaňļ,¬†so We sent against them a ňĻbitterňļ wind and forces you could not see.¬†And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  33,10,"ňĻRememberňļ when they came at you from east and west,¬†when your eyes grew wild ňĻin horrorňļ and your hearts jumped into your throats, and you entertained ňĻconflictingňļ thoughts about Allah"
  33,11,"Then and there the believers were put to the test, and were violently shaken"
  33,12,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, ‚ÄúAllah and His Messenger have promised us nothing but delusion!‚ÄĚ"
  33,13,"And ňĻrememberňļ when a group of them said, ‚ÄúO people of Yathrib!¬†There is no point in you staying ňĻhereňļ, so retreat!‚ÄĚ Another group of them asked the Prophet‚Äôs permission ňĻto leaveňļ, saying, ‚ÄúOur homes are vulnerable,‚ÄĚ while ňĻin factňļ they were not vulnerable. They only wished to flee"
  33,14,"Had their city been sacked from all sides and they had been asked to abandon faith, they would have done so with little hesitation"
  33,15,They had already pledged to Allah earlier never to turn their backs ňĻin retreatňļ. And a pledge to Allah must be answered for
  33,16,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúFleeing will not benefit you if you ňĻtry toňļ escape a natural or violent death. ňĻIf it is not your time,ňļ you will only be allowed enjoyment for a little while.‚ÄĚ"
  33,17,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho can put you out of Allah‚Äôs reach if He intends to harm you or show you mercy?‚ÄĚ They can never find any protector or helper besides Allah"
  33,18,"Allah knows well those among you who discourage ňĻothers from fightingňļ, saying ňĻsecretlyňļ to their brothers, ‚ÄúStay with us,‚ÄĚ and who themselves hardly take part in fighting"
  33,19,"ňĻThey areňļ totally unwilling to assist you. When danger comes, you see them staring at you with their eyes rolling like someone in the throes of death. But once the danger is over, they slash you with razor-sharp tongues, ravenous for ňĻworldlyňļ gains. Such people have not ňĻtrulyňļ believed, so Allah has rendered their deeds void. And that is easy for Allah"
  33,20,"They ňĻstillňļ think that the enemy alliance has not ňĻyetňļ withdrawn. And if the allies were to come ňĻagainňļ, the hypocrites would wish to be away in the desert among nomadic Arabs, ňĻonlyňļ asking for news about you ňĻbelieversňļ. And if the hypocrites were in your midst, they would hardly take part in the fight"
  33,21,"Indeed, in the Messenger of Allah you have an excellent example for whoever has hope in Allah and the Last Day, and remembers Allah often"
  33,22,"When the believers saw the enemy alliance, they said, ‚ÄúThis is what Allah and His Messenger had promised us. The promise of Allah and His Messenger has come true.‚ÄĚ And this only increased them in faith and submission"
  33,23,"Among the believers are men who have proven true to what they pledged to Allah.¬†Some of them have fulfilled their pledge ňĻwith their livesňļ, others are waiting ňĻtheir turnňļ. They have never changed ňĻtheir commitmentňļ in the least"
  33,24,"ňĻIt all happenedňļ so Allah may reward the faithful for their faithfulness, and punish the hypocrites if He wills or turn to them ňĻin mercyňļ. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,25,"And Allah drove back the disbelievers in their rage, totally empty-handed. And Allah spared the believers from fighting. For Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  33,26,"And He brought down those from the People of the Book¬†who supported the enemy alliance from their own strongholds, and cast horror into their hearts. You ňĻbelieversňļ killed some, and took others captive"
  33,27,"He has also caused you to take over their lands, homes, and wealth, as well as lands you have not yet set foot on. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  33,28,"O Prophet! Say to your wives, ‚ÄúIf you desire the life of this world and its luxury, then come, I will give you a ňĻsuitableňļ compensation ňĻfor divorceňļ and let you go graciously"
  33,29,"But if you desire Allah and His Messenger and the ňĻeverlastingňļ Home of the Hereafter, then Surely Allah has prepared a great reward for those of you who do good.‚ÄĚ"
  33,30,"O wives of the Prophet! If any of you were to commit a blatant misconduct, the punishment would be doubled for her. And that is easy for Allah"